Preconditions:
The input matrix `grid` must be a square matrix of size `n x n`.
The elements of the matrix `grid` must be binary, i.e., they can only have values 0 or The matrix `grid` must represent a valid grid with obstacles (1) and clear paths (0).

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the length of the shortest clear path in the matrix.
If there is no clear path in the matrix, the method should return -1.